In a bowl, combine the brownie mix, water, oil and egg until well blended. Spread into a greased and floured 12-in. pizza pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 25 minutes. In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla until combined. Spread over brownie crust. Bake 15 minutes longer or until topping is set. Cool on a wire rack. Just before serving, arrange strawberries and bananas over topping; drizzle with chocolate. Refrigerate leftovers.